name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
A Russian surface-to-air missile caused the crash of an Azerbaijan Airlines passenger plane in Kazakhstan on Wednesday, Azerbaijan government sources confirmed to Euronews.
The missile was fired at Flight 8432 during a drone flight over Grozny, the source revealed, exploding next to the plane during flight, hitting passengers and crew with shrapnel. Despite the pilot's request for an emergency landing, the plane was not allowed to land at any Russian airport, but was ordered to fly to Aktau, Kazakhstan.
If the preliminary data is confirmed, this will be the second time in a decade that the Russian military has destroyed a civilian airliner, following the MH17 crash. This time, Russian citizens as well as citizens of neighboring countries have become casualties.
